  <div class="box">
    <h3>Data Visualization & Graph Layer</h3>
    <p>The core design challenge for charts was making visualizations feel native rather than embedded from elsewhere — animation, labeling, and source attribution were treated as deliberate interface moments, not decoration. Responses could contain structured tables alongside prose, keeping data scannable without fragmenting the reading experience.</p>
    <p>The data catalog was searchable and filterable, built around the assumption that users arrive with a question, not a dataset. Findability was a first-class concern: the interface had to support both directed queries and exploratory browsing without making either feel like a workaround.</p>
  </div>

